[00:09.77]Why did the writer complain to the people behind him?|为什么作者会向他身后的人抱怨呢？
[00:15.91]Last week I went to the theatre.|上周我去看了电影。
[00:19.39]I had a very good seat.|我的座位非常好。
[00:22.07]The play was very interesting.|这出戏非常有趣。
[00:25.10]I did not enjoy it.|我并不喜欢它。
[00:27.43]A young man and a young woman were sitting behind me.|一个年轻男子和一个年轻女子坐在我后面。
[00:31.96]They were talking loudly.|他们说话的声音很大。
[00:34.59]I got very angry.|我非常生气。
[00:37.41]I could not hear the actors.|我听不到演员们的声音。
[00:40.64]I turned round.|我转过身来。
[00:42.80]I looked at the man and the woman angrily.|我愤怒地瞪着那个男人和那个女人。
[00:47.27]They did not pay any attention.|他们根本没有理会。
[00:50.69]In the end, I could not bear it.|最后，我实在无法忍受下去了。
[00:54.98]I turned round again.|我又转过身去。
[00:57.75]'I can't hear a word!' I said angrily.|“我一个字都听不见！”我愤怒地说道。
[01:03.45]'It's none of your business,'|“这不关你的事。”
[01:06.27]the young man said rudely.|那个年轻人粗鲁地说道。
